Yep, that is &quot;YACD&quot;, not &quot;YASD&quot;.

I knew the level was going to be interesting as soon as I saw &quot;You sense
a horde of monsters. You sense something dangerous 33 times.&quot; My initial
guess was &quot;Troll pit,&quot; but it wasn't ... fortunately, as it turns out.

I quaffed a !Enlightenment I had on me for use the next time I got an
interesting level. It revealed a level whose lower right corner
contained a suspiciously troll-pit-shaped room but containing a couple
of weapons or armors. I didn't see any other pit-like rooms anywhere,
though there were several oddly-shaped ones, including a big room
flooded with water with some trees and a central &quot;castle&quot; in the middle
of this &quot;moat&quot;.

Naturally, I started by exploring away from the suspected pit heading to
the top left corner, then left and down and right. In the top left area
I got a bunch of red messages about premonitions of death, and was
afflicted with the fear status ailment! At first I thought it was some
unnoticed monster attacking with a scary and unfamiliar spell, and I
checked my HP first -- normal -- and then the map nearby -- unoccupied
except for one lonely creature with the symbol '@'. Then I saw that the
depth &quot;Lev 44&quot; in the bottom right corner was dark red.

That was the *level feeling message*?! Vanilla never did anything like
that. Even Zangband gave a &quot;bad feeling&quot; sometimes, but never like that...

I proceed very, very cautiously to kick the can of everything I find in
the parts of the level that look relatively normal. Next is the
moat-room, where a sharpshooter does a bit of damage before falling to a
barrage of Doom Bolt (whose fail is now low enough to use as a workhorse
damage-dealer when mana conservation is unimportant). That's the worst
thing there and the only unfamiliar thing, and it's not actually out of
depth.

From this room I can creep far enough right to image the suspected pit
with temp ESP ... and it's swarming with &amp;s which I hadn't seen all game
(or indeed, in Angband ever). Turns out the &amp;s are Erinyes, though, a
familiar and relatively tame monster from Angband tradition, despite the
new symbol.

I risk a closer approach and there's only a handful of anything else in
there -- Vrocks, which I know will strip my hide if I let them get
within melee range, but are otherwise harmless to a fella with resist
blindness.

There is a large empty room some distance from the pit, such that I can
rest in it without attracting demons but I can also go to one corner and
lure some of them to approach through various corridors.

It takes a lot of dispel evils, and resting. The odd Erinyes summon of a
Bodak or Lamia slows things not at all due to the power of m2c to affect
everything evil in sight. Soon, I need to move closer to the pit to lure
out what's left. A dragon, some stone trolls, and one or two other
random monsters interrupt and fall to Doom Bolt if they aren't dispelled
by Dispel Evil. Once or twice low mana and plenty of monsters still
nearby leads me to use acid bolt rods and blinking; once or twice I feel
the need to teleport and regroup.

When all is said and done, the floor is littered with junk in the room I
used as the killing field and in the surrounding corridors. There's a
ton of weapons and armor none of which are worth keeping -- even the
excellent ones. A convenient Staff of Perception dropped and I used it
to ID the excellent items, and what were they but really heavy armor of
resist acid (*yawn* already got artifact body armor at 1/20 the weight)
and a shield of resist cold or some such. There's no fewer than six new
item types -- two potion types, two rod types, a mushroom type, and
scroll type. Needless to say I test these only when there's no enemy
left nearby. Mushroom is for berserking; useless for a caster so I dump
the remaining one. Two rods of polymorph and one of sense surroundings.
Both look worth trying to sell but not use; sense surroundings is
something I already have via a perception skill talent. One potion is
restore wisdom; the other is strength -- not restore strength, just
plain strength. And there are two of them.

Statgain time! Indeed, potions of int and wis dropped as well, and two
of charisma. An amulet of int +4 dropped, replacing my +3 one. A ring of
sustain body. Amulet of wis +4 I have no use for.

The items in the pit (odd, for there to be floor items in a pit) prove
to be relatively uninteresting.

When all is said and done, I've had a tiny bit of XP drain (a summoned
Lamia got close) and my stats are intact (the Sustain Body dropped
earlier in the level and I wore it during the entire pit wiping, so the
Erinyes couldn't drain my strength).

Oh, and did I mention I racked up nearly 55,000 experience points?
Enough to use a pittance to remove the drain and a ton more to get
almost everything up to 70%. That gives me Mists of Death and, from the
look, every town book spell.

I've seen deep books now -- both times priestly books. One was dropped
by one of today's Erinyes, of all the things to be carrying such a book.
It got sold for a nice chunk of change.

My score is nearly 800 now thanks to the Vrocks, and I have the sense
charges talent apparently from raising magical devices. Sense charges
doesn't seem to work exactly like learn magic; I can't seem to use it on
rings or amulets with unknown pluses, for example.

Most of my important spells have low fails now, and the shadow warping
type spells are coming down in fail. Str is now 14, which should help
with burden slowing a lot. Every important ability is green or better,
and all but Saving Throw blue or better...

