the shopkeeper always tries to make a set profit on the inventory he brings
in and would/should always want to have the higher selling items to make
more profit...

50% profit on a single $5 item is $2.50 profit
50% profit on a stack of $5 items (qty 20) is $50.00
50% profit on a single $100 item is $50.00

(well,... actually, he/she would really want the items that will sell
faster, so he can buy food for his family that day... but who's going to
code in a supply/demand system for shopkeeper pricing?)

so if he can afford to lose the amount he invested in a low cost item, he
would want that higher priced item to sell off for a greater profit
(assuming fixed percentage profit system like most (all?) roguelike games)

