Yes, you are quite right here, and it goes back to your comments on the
squelching issues a little while back.

Perhaps the (initially drastic) way to deal with this is to drop the shops. Have
a temple selling restore stat &quot;service&quot; (at some unreasonable price like 5,000),
Magic shop sells useful scrolls (read WoR and Teleport only here, at about 500
and 300 respectively). Dump the alchemy shop. On the note of price, make Restore
Life Levels another &quot;service&quot;, at perhaps 3,000 or so, and CCW potions not for
sale. CSW sold at 500 or so, and CLW at 50 - this way they are useful to begin
with, and the upgrade is smoother. Stops munchkin-stocking of CCW potions.

Weapon and Armour can be combined to a &quot;adventurers shop&quot;, and contains less
quality items - smaller weapons, nothing above +0,+0, no longbows, katanas, no
armour over [6,+0], no iron helms, large leather shields, gauntlets, hard
leather boots.

Dump the black market, fun that it is the temptation to scum it is unreasonable
(was better when shops were 1-6 only, but I'd miss the home).

Leaves only food, light and tool shop (1), adventurers shop (2), temple (3),
Magic Shop (4), and home (5).

Make sure nothing will accept items bought from the dungeon except for maybe the
adventurers taking artifacts.

This will probably help the TMJ issue IMHO. As only useful drops are worth
investigating, it will be much more immediately obvious what drops tend to be
generally junk.

